{
  "stem": "17426.7",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 177.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as we began to smell smoke, we knew that the ship was afire and sinking.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My brother and I and the others that were with me were trying to open the door, but it was impossible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it took some time, like an hour and a half or two in which we were dying in there from the smoke.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Till finally someone opened the door and everyone was pushing against the door.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This by itself was torture, to get to the door and be able to get out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when we came up both stairs up to the upper deck were completely in fire.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We could neither penetrate one or the other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so we ran [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] from one end of the ship to the other trying to find a way to get out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Till we finally came to a men's room with toilets with about [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] two feet opening on top, the deck.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were already other inmates there that were being tried to lift out onto the deck by ropes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in this panic, in this melee, one wanted to save his life stepped on top of the other, preventing him from being pulled up.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this only [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] lengthened the time at which people could be saved.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And finally I was pulled up, and I helped my brother by leaning down.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Somebody held on to my legs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Pulled him up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I think it didn't take long after that, and the fire reached-- the smoke reached that room, and whoever was still down there was gone.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "No one ever came up again.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
